# Documentation Update Rules

When making any changes to the codebase, always update the documentation and translations accordingly.

## Documentation Updates

1. **Update source documentation**: Modify `.rst` files in `docs/docs/` to reflect code changes
2. **Update changelog**: Add entries to `docs/docs/changelog.rst` for significant changes

## Translation Workflow

1. **Generate translation templates** (only for local testing): From `docs/` run `sphinx-build -b gettext . _build/gettext` to generate `.pot` files
2. **Update translation files** (only for local testing): From `docs/` run `sphinx-intl update -p _build/gettext -l ru` to update `.po` files in `docs/locale/ru/LC_MESSAGES/`
3. **Translate new strings**: Edit Russian translations in `.po` files for any new or modified strings
4. **Keep PO reference lines**: Do not remove or alter `#:` reference lines (e.g. `#: ../../docs/examples.rst:3 b90cdb1602eb41d0b4027cd928290c3f`). Sphinx uses the file path, line number and hash to match translations; keep these as generated
5. **In repository**: Keep only `.po` files. Do not commit `.mo` files — Read the Docs compiles `.mo` during the documentation build (see `.readthedocs.yaml`)

## Cleanup After Testing

After running gettext/update-po or building docs locally, always remove generated artifacts:

- **Remove build directory**: Delete `docs/_build/` (e.g. PowerShell: `Remove-Item -Recurse -Force docs\_build`)
- **Remove all .mo files**: Delete every `*.mo` under `docs/locale/` (e.g. PowerShell: `Get-ChildItem -Path docs\locale -Filter *.mo -Recurse | Remove-Item`)
- **Check git status**: Ensure no `_build/` or `.mo` files are staged or committed

## Workflow Example (Windows, PowerShell)

```powershell
# 1. Make code changes
# 2. Update .rst files in docs/docs/
# 3. (Optional, for testing) Update translations
cd docs
sphinx-build -b gettext . _build/gettext
sphinx-intl update -p _build/gettext -l ru
# 4. Edit .po files with new translations (keep #: reference lines with hashes)
# 5. (Optional) Test build
sphinx-build -b html -D language=en . _build/html/en
sphinx-build -b html -D language=ru . _build/html/ru
# 6. Clean up: remove _build and all .mo files
Remove-Item -Recurse -Force _build
Get-ChildItem -Path locale -Filter *.mo -Recurse | Remove-Item
cd ..
```

**Important**: Never commit `docs/_build/` or any `docs/locale/**/*.mo`. Only `.po` files belong in the repo; `.mo` is built on Read the Docs.
